title: Jimi Hendrix - South Bank Show
description:
Here is a nice bootleg. Check my account for more classic bootlegs.

Please enjoy, share with friends and please seed :)

The Southbank TV Special (Collector's Disc / 2006 / DVD-R)

ITVs Southbank TV Special, 1986 plus "Hoepla", VPRO Vitus Studio, Bussum 10.11.67
Bonus:
/ Veronika Hjort photos (from Swedish TV "Landet Rundt" (Around the Country) 12.11.05)
/ "Pass It On" Rare Video Collection: Konserthallen, Liseberg, Gothenburg 19.05.67
(8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound from "Popside", Radiohuset, Stockholm 24.05.67)
/ Stora Scenen, GrÃ¶na Lund, Stockholm 24.05.67 + Stora Scenen, GrÃ¶na Lund, Stockholm 04.09.67
+ Stora Scenen, GrÃ¶na Lund, Stockholm 11.09.67 Composite (Dubbed Sound from Stockholm 11.09.67)
/ London Film Premiere 18.10.67
/ Generation Club, New York City, NY 07.04.68 [Jam with Buddy Guy] (from the unreleased
D.A.Pennenbaker film "Wake At Generation")
/ Beat Monster Konzert, Hallenstadion, Zurich 31.05.68 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Lorensbergs Circus, Gothenburg 08.01.69 [2nd Show] (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Civic Center, Baltimore, MD 16.05.69 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Madison Square Garden, New York City, NY 18.05.69 (16mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Toronto Courthouse 19.06.69 (Sound Dubbed from Maple Leaf Gardens, Toronto 03.05.69)
/ Denver Pop Festival, Miles High Stadium, Denver, CO 29.06.69 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Berkeley Community Theatre, Berkeley, CA 30.05.70 [2nd Show] (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Sicks Stadium, Seattle, WA 26.07.70 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Veijlby Risskov Hallen, Aarhus 02.09.70 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ KB Hallen, Copenhagen 03.09.70 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
/ Love And Peace Festival, Insel Fehmarn 06.09.70 (8mm; Silent footage with Dubbed Sound)
notes:
- Roy Buchanan was formerly believed to have participated in the 07.04.68 jam, but this is
wrong. The featured guitarist is most likely Dave Woods, with Ed "Bugs" Gregory on bass, and
possibly Glenway McTeer on drums
